                " \n \nPROGRAMME MANAGER EPWP - ECOD19182\nClosing Date: 2024-04-08\nAssignment Type: Permanent\nDivision: Economic Infrastructure, Job Creation & Skills Development Division (2019)\nDepartment: Economic Development Department (2019)\nProvince: Gauteng\n\nPurpose:\n \nResponsibilities\nDevelop and implement labour intensive public employment strategies, programmes and plans.\nCoordinate, manage and mobilize strategic internal and external stakeholder relationships.\nEnsure the effective implementation and integration of programme management frameworks, tools and systems.\nAdvise stakeholder departments, municipal entities, service providers and related stakeholders on best practice and technical knowledge relating to EPWP.\nDevelop a EPWP monitoring, evaluate and reporting framework to measure effective implementation principles in the municipality.\nCoordinate overall EPWP related priorities with stakeholder Departments, Municipal Entities, Service Providers and all related stakeholders.\nDevelop annual joint operating plan to meet established annual objectives and organise and prioritise tasks and work processes needed to achieve the overall objectives.\nManage and maintain governance and risk management system of the functional area.\nParticipate in and implement budget planning principles on stakeholder department's budget to determine their contribution to the overall annual EPWP targets.\nManage and ensure a customer service-oriented environment as well as determine and facilitate people management and related activities in the division.\n \nJob Requirements\nB Degree in Public Administration or Development Studies or Social Sciences or relevant equivalent NQF Level 7 qualification\n5 - 8 years' experience in local government administration or a similar environment\nA valid driver's license.\n \n \nEnquiries: Tel: 0860 54 3000\n \nThe successful candidate will be required to sign a performance contract as per Council resolution.\n\n \nCandidates may be requested to submit proof of the NQF level applicable to the qualifications they have obtained.\n \nShould candidates not be informed of the outcome of the application within six weeks of the closing date, it should be regarded as having been unsuccessful. The City of Ekurhuleni subscribes to the principles of the Employment Equity Act and reserves the right to appoint, not appoint or to appoint laterally\n \nPreferred:\nRemuneration: R 801780.0 to R 1099896.0 - Basic plus benefits\nContact:\nTelephone:\n \nAPPLY NOW!\n \n \n \n ",
